post_cb({"3698751": {"ParentId": "3698446", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<p>Not possible to keep inside.\nOnly const static integral data members are allowed to initialized inside a class or struct.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "443190", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "3698751", "Score": "0", "CreationDate": "2010-09-13T08:15:25.317", "LastActivityDate": "2010-09-13T08:15:25.317"}, "3698475": {"ParentId": "3698446", "PostTypeId": "2", "CommentCount": "5", "Body": "<p>Static variable of a class have to be defined explicitly in the namespace scope only once (irrespective of wheter they are further cv qualified or not).</p>\n<p>In the .cpp file (e.g in <code>&lt;ClassName&gt;.cpp</code>), in the global namespace (assuming your class is in global namespace), define it as follows (assuming an appropriate constructor exists in QString)</p>\n<p>NB: I missed 'const' in the definition below</p>\n<pre><code>const QString &lt;ClassName&gt;::ALARM_ERROR_IMAGE = \"error.png\";\n</code></pre>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_3698446_3698475_0\">$9.4.2/2 - \"The declaration of a\n  static data member in its class\n  definition is not a definition and may\n  be of an incomplete type other than\n  cv-qualified void. The definition for\n  a static data member shall appear in a\n  namespace scope enclosing the member\u2019s\n  class definition. In the definition at\n  namespace scope, the name of the\n  static data member shall be qualified\n  by its class name using the ::\n  operator.\"</p>\n</blockquote>\n", "OwnerUserId": "418110", "LastEditorUserId": "418110", "LastEditDate": "2010-09-13T08:13:18.033", "Id": "3698475", "Score": "2", "CreationDate": "2010-09-13T07:21:36.927", "LastActivityDate": "2010-09-13T08:13:18.033"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_3698446_3698475_0": {"section_id": 5907, "quality": 0.9285714285714286, "length": 39}}, "n3337": {"so_3698446_3698475_0": {"section_id": 5679, "quality": 0.9285714285714286, "length": 39}}, "n4659": {"so_3698446_3698475_0": {"section_id": 7389, "quality": 0.8809523809523809, "length": 37}}}, "3698446": {"CommentCount": "0", "ViewCount": "529", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "428287", "CreationDate": "2010-09-13T07:16:38.457", "LastActivityDate": "2010-09-13T08:15:25.317", "Title": "Initilizing value for a const data", "AcceptedAnswerId": "3698475", "LastEditDate": "2010-09-13T07:24:11.833", "Id": "3698446", "Score": "1", "Body": "<p>Following code is in my c++ class</p>\n<pre><code>static const  QString ALARM_ERROR_IMAGE ;\n</code></pre>\n<p>i want to initilize </p>\n<pre><code>ALARM_ERROR_IMAGE          = \"error.png\";\n</code></pre>\n<p>Is it possible to initilize <code>error.png</code> to <code>static const QString ALARM_ERROR_IMAGE</code> \nWant to keep it inside class</p>\n", "Tags": "<c++><visual-c++><qt><qt4>", "OwnerUserId": "278521", "AnswerCount": "2"}});